{"id": "EUVD-2018-8637", "enisaUuid": "7164e1cf-2f0f-3d61-987a-8d837e1374ee", "description": "Samba from version 4.3.0 and before versions 4.7.12, 4.8.7 and 4.9.3 are vulnerable to a denial of service. When configured to accept smart-card authentication, Samba's KDC will call talloc_free() twice on the same memory if the principal in a validly signed certificate does not match the principal in the AS-REQ. This is only possible after authentication with a trusted certificate. talloc is robust against further corruption from a double-free with talloc_free() and directly calls abort(), terminating the KDC process.", "datePublished": "2018-11-28T14:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T10:32:54", "baseScore": 5.7, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:R/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-16841.html", "https://www.debian.org/security/2018/dsa-4345", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-16841", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2018-16841.html", "https://security.archlinux.org/CVE-2018-16841", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/106023", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3827-2/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3827-1/", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20181127-0001/", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=CVE-2018-16841", "https://www.samba.org/samba/security/CVE-2018-16841.html", "https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202003-52"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-16841"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 9.42, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "09e7dfb4-d377-3aa7-93b4-0cffbd11bc69", "product": {"name": "Samba"}, "product_version": "4.8.7"}, {"id": "240281db-4b5d-34c2-bf7c-d359f0ec1abb", "product": {"name": "Samba"}, "product_version": "4.7.12"}, {"id": "4efbaa98-7680-33d1-8a32-c4ac5fcf0033", "product": {"name": "Samba"}, "product_version": "4.9.3"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "4a097c62-e8a7-30fe-8fb1-74a9bd3b8bb6", "vendor": {"name": "[UNKNOWN]"}}], "isExploited": false}